FBIS4-22062 "jptot017__l94001" JPRS-TOT-94-017-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 23 April 1994 EAST ASIA THAILAND Bomb Explosion Kills Six in Nakhon Si Thammarat Bomb Explosion Kills Six in Nakhon Si Thammarat Railway Station Targetted BK2304081494 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 23 Apr 94 BK2304081494 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network Thai BFN [Text] A Public Relations Department correspondent reported from Nakhon Si Thammarat Province that a bomb exploded at the railway station in Nakhon Si Thammarat at about noon. The motive of the explosion is unknown. Six persons were killed instantly and several were injured. Second Lieutenant Thanaphong Chakkaphak, Nakhon Si Thammarat deputy governor, and police officials went to the scene to investigate the incident. Those injured were rushed to the Maharat Hospital of Nakhon Si Thammarat for treatment.
